description: The process of transferring a fucosyl group to an N-glycan. An N-glycan is the carbohydrate portion of an N-glycoprotein when attached to a nitrogen from asparagine or arginine side-chains.

name: negative regulation of protein refolding
description: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of protein refolding. Protein refolding is the process carried out by a cell that restores the biological activity of an unfolded or misfolded protein, using helper proteins such as chaperones.

name: cellular response to reactive nitrogen species
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a reactive nitrogen species stimulus.

name: ciliary basal body
description: A membrane-tethered, short cylindrical array of microtubules and associated proteins found at the base of a eukaryotic cilium (also called flagellum) that is similar in structure to a centriole and derives from it. The cilium basal body is the site of assembly and remodelling of the cilium and serves as a nucleation site for axoneme growth. As well as anchoring the cilium, it is thought to provide a selective gateway regulating the entry of ciliary proteins and vesicles by intraflagellar transport.

name: fucosylation
description: The covalent attachment of a fucosyl group to an acceptor molecule.

name: protein O-linked fucosylation
description: The process of transferring a fucosyl group to a serine or threonine residues in a protein acceptor molecule, to form an O-linked protein-sugar linkage.

name: slit diaphragm assembly
description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a slit diaphragm, specialized cell-cell junction found between the interdigitating foot processes of the glomerular epithelium (the podocytes) in the vertebrate kidney, which is adapted for facilitating glomerular filtration.

name: iris morphogenesis
description: The process in which the iris is generated and organized. The iris is an anatomical structure in the eye whose opening forms the pupil. The iris is responsible for controlling the diameter and size of the pupil and the amount of light reaching the retina.

name: ciliary body morphogenesis
description: The process in which the ciliary body generated and organized. The ciliary body is the circumferential tissue inside the eye composed of the ciliary muscle and ciliary processes.

name: protein K6-linked ubiquitination
description: A protein ubiquitination process in which a polymer of ubiquitin, formed by linkages between lysine residues at position 6 of the ubiquitin monomers, is added to a protein. K6-linked ubiquitination is involved in DNA repair.

name: positive regulation of mRNA catabolic process
description: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of a mRNA catabolic process, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of RNA, ribonucleic acid, one of the two main type of nucleic acid, consisting of a long, unbranched macromolecule formed from ribonucleotides joined in 3',5'-phosphodiester linkage.

name: snRNA import into nucleus
description: The directed movement of snRNA, small nuclear ribonucleic acid into the nucleus.

name: positive regulation of mitochondrial membrane permeability involved in apoptotic process
description: Any positive regulation of mitochondrial membrane permeability that is involved in apoptotic process.

name: gall bladder development
description: The progression of the gall bladder over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The gall bladder is a cavitated organ that stores bile.

name: hepatic duct development
description: The progression of the hepatic duct over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The hepatic duct is the duct that leads from the liver to the common bile duct.

name: ubiquinone binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with ubiquinone, a quinone derivative with a tail of isoprene units.

name: hepatoblast differentiation
description: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a hepatoblast. A hepatoblast is a cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into hepatocytes and cholangiocytes.

name: calcidiol binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with calcidiol.

name: triokinase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: D-glyceraldehyde + ATP = D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).

name: trimethyllysine dioxygenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + N(6),N(6),N(6)-trimethyl-L-lysine + O(2) = 3-hydroxy-N(6),N(6),N(6)-trimethyl-L-lysine + CO(2) + succinate.

name: maintenance of Golgi location
description: Any process in which the Golgi is maintained in a specific location within a cell and prevented from moving elsewhere.

name: embryonic eye morphogenesis
description: The process occurring in the embryo by which the anatomical structures of the post-embryonic eye are generated and organized.

name: establishment of Golgi localization
description: The directed movement of the Golgi to a specific location.

name: focal adhesion assembly
description: The aggregation and bonding together of a set of components to form a focal adhesion, a complex of intracellular signaling and structural proteins that provides a structural link between the internal actin cytoskeleton and the ECM, and also function as a locus of signal transduction activity.

name: UDP-glucuronate decarboxylase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(+) + UDP-alpha-D-glucuronate = CO(2) + UDP-alpha-D-xylose.

name: regulation of dendritic spine morphogenesis
description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine morphogenesis, the process in which the anatomical structures of a dendritic spine are generated and organized. A dendritic spine is a protrusion from a dendrite and a specialized subcellular compartment involved in synaptic transmission.

name: negative regulation of dendritic spine morphogenesis
description: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine morphogenesis, the process in which the anatomical structures of a dendritic spine are generated and organized. A dendritic spine is a protrusion from a dendrite and a specialized subcellular compartment involved in synaptic transmission.

name: positive regulation of dendritic spine morphogenesis
description: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine morphogenesis, the process in which the anatomical structures of a dendritic spine are generated and organized. A dendritic spine is a protrusion from a dendrite and a specialized subcellular compartment involved in synaptic transmission.

name: lithocholic acid binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with lithocholic acid.

name: chenodeoxycholic acid binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with chenodeoxycholic acid.

name: common bile duct development
description: The progression of the common bile duct over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The common bile duct is formed from the joining of the common hepatic duct running from the liver, and the cystic duct running from the gall bladder. The common bile duct transports bile from the liver and gall bladder to the intestine.

name: cell differentiation involved in kidney development
description: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells of the kidney as it progresses from its formation to the mature state.

name: actin filament capping
description: The binding of a protein or protein complex to the end of an actin filament, thus preventing the addition, exchange or removal of further actin subunits.

name: compound eye corneal lens development
description: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the corneal lens in the compound eye over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The corneal lens is a chitinous extracellular secretion of the four underlying cone cells and the pigment cells.

name: post-embryonic eye morphogenesis
description: The process, occurring after embryonic development, by which the anatomical structures of the eye are generated and organized. The eye is the organ of sight.

name: olfactory bulb mitral cell layer development
description: The progression of the olfactory bulb mitral cell layer over time from its initial formation until its mature state. The mitral cell layer is composed of pyramidal neurons whose cell bodies are located between the granule cell layer and the plexiform layer.

name: regulation of cartilage development
description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of cartilage development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cartilage over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cartilage is a connective tissue dominated by extracellular matrix containing collagen type II and large amounts of proteoglycan, particularly chondroitin sulfate.

name: positive regulation of cartilage development
description: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of cartilage development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cartilage over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cartilage is a connective tissue dominated by extracellular matrix containing collagen type II and large amounts of proteoglycan, particularly chondroitin sulfate.

name: negative regulation of cartilage development
description: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of cartilage development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cartilage over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cartilage is a connective tissue dominated by extracellular matrix containing collagen type II and large amounts of proteoglycan, particularly chondroitin sulfate.

name: epithelial cell differentiation involved in mammary gland alveolus development
description: The process in which a relatively unspecialized epithelial cell becomes a more specialized epithelial cell of the mammary gland alveolus.

name: endodermal digestive tract morphogenesis
description: The process in which the anatomical structures of the endodermal digestive tract are generated and organized. The endodermal digestive tract includes those portions of the digestive tract that are derived from endoderm.

name: visceral serous pericardium development
description: The progression of the visceral serous pericardium from its formation to the mature structure. The visceral serous pericardium is the inner layer of the pericardium.

name: secretion by lung epithelial cell involved in lung growth
description: The controlled release of liquid by a lung epithelial cell that contributes to an increase in size of the lung as part of its development.

name: uterus morphogenesis
description: The process in which anatomical structures of the uterus are generated and organized.

name: developmental pigmentation
description: The developmental process that results in the deposition of coloring matter in an organism, tissue or cell.

name: eye pigmentation
description: Establishment of a pattern of pigment in the eye of an organism.

name: UDP-glucuronate 5'-epimerase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-alpha-D-glucuronate = UDP-L-iduronate.

name: membrane organization
description: A process which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a membrane. A membrane is a double layer of lipid molecules that encloses all cells, and, in eukaryotes, many organelles; may be a single or double lipid bilayer; also includes associated proteins.

name: membrane fusion
description: The membrane organization process that joins two lipid bilayers to form a single membrane.

name: cardiac muscle tissue regeneration
description: The regrowth of cardiac muscle tissue to repair injured or damaged muscle fibers in the postnatal stage.

name: establishment of endothelial barrier
description: The establishment of a barrier between endothelial cell layers, such as those in the brain, lung or intestine, to exert specific and selective control over the passage of water and solutes, thus allowing formation and maintenance of compartments that differ in fluid and solute composition.

name: eyelid development in camera-type eye
description: The progression of the eyelid in a camera-type eye from its formation to the mature state. The eyelid is a membranous cover that helps protect and lubricate the eye.

name: positive regulation of eye pigmentation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of a pattern of pigment in the eye of an organism.

name: regulation of developmental pigmentation
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the developmental process that results in the deposition of coloring matter in an organism.

name: negative regulation of eye pigmentation
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of a pattern of pigment in the eye of an organism.

name: regulation of eye pigmentation
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of a pattern of pigment in the eye of an organism.

name: response to salt
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a salt stimulus.

name: positive regulation of lateral motor column neuron migration
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of lateral motor column neuron migration.

name: GMP reductase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: IMP + NADP(+) + NH(4)(+) = GMP + 2 H(+) + NADPH.

name: GMP synthase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + xanthosine 5'-phosphate + NH3 = AMP + diphosphate + GMP.

name: long-chain fatty acid transport
description: The directed movement of long-chain fatty acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. A long-chain fatty acid is a fatty acid with a chain length between C13 and C22.

name: fatty acid transport
description: The directed movement of fatty acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Fatty acids are aliphatic monocarboxylic acids liberated from naturally occurring fats and oils by hydrolysis.

name: GMP synthase (glutamine-hydrolyzing) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + xanthosine 5'-phosphate + L-glutamine + H2O = AMP + diphosphate + GMP + L-glutamate.

name: GPI-anchor transamidase activity
description: Catalysis of the formation of the linkage between a protein and a glycosylphosphatidylinositol anchor. The reaction probably occurs by subjecting a peptide bond to nucleophilic attack by the amino group of ethanolamine-GPI, transferring the protein from a signal peptide to the GPI anchor.

name: GTPase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: GTP + H2O = GDP + phosphate.

name: tetracycline transport
description: The directed movement of tetracycline into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Tetracycline is a broad spectrum antibiotic that blocks binding of aminoacyl tRNA to the ribosomes of both Gram-positive and Gram-negative organisms (and those of organelles).

name: negative regulation of cell proliferation involved in mesonephros development
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation involved in mesonephros development.

name: peroxisomal membrane transport
description: The directed movement of substances to, from or across the peroxisomal membrane.

name: GTP cyclohydrolase I activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: GTP + H2O = formate + 7,8-dihydroneopterin 3'-triphosphate.

name: sterol transport
description: The directed movement of sterols into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Sterols are steroids with one or more hydroxyl groups and a hydrocarbon side-chain in the molecule.

name: aminophospholipid transport
description: The directed movement of aminophospholipids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Aminophospholipids contain phosphoric acid as a mono- or diester and an amino (NH2) group.

name: negative regulation of dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation.

name: positive regulation of dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation.

name: IMP cyclohydrolase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: IMP + H2O = 5-formamido-1-(5-phosphoribosyl)imidazole-4-carboxamide.

name: phospholipid transport
description: The directed movement of phospholipids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Phospholipids are any lipids containing phosphoric acid as a mono- or diester.

name: IMP dehydrogenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: inosine 5'-phosphate + NAD+ + H2O = xanthosine 5'-phosphate + NADH + H+.

name: L-iditol 2-dehydrogenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: L-iditol + NAD+ = L-sorbose + NADH + H+.

name: positive regulation of Arp2/3 complex-mediated actin nucleation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of Arp2/3 complex-mediated actin nucleation.

name: plasma membrane long-chain fatty acid transport
description: The directed movement of long-chain fatty acids across the plasma membrane. A long-chain fatty acid is a fatty acid with a chain length between C13 and C22.

name: peroxisomal long-chain fatty acid import
description: The directed movement of long-chain fatty acids into a peroxisome. A long-chain fatty acid is a fatty acid with a chain length between C13 and C22.

name: negative regulation of peptidyl-cysteine S-nitrosylation
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of peptidyl-cysteine S-nitrosylation.

name: negative regulation of calcium ion import into sarcoplasmic reticulum
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of calcium ion import into sarcoplasmic reticulum.

name: calcitriol binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with calcitriol. Calcitriol (1,25-dihydroxycholecalciferol) is the hormonally active form of vitamin D3.

name: positive regulation of histone H3-K9 acetylation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of histone H3-K9 acetylation.

name: regulation of histone H3-K9 acetylation
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of histone H3-K9 acetylation.

name: alkylbase DNA N-glycosylase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: DNA with alkylated base + H2O = DNA with abasic site + alkylated base. This reaction is the hydrolysis of DNA by cleavage of the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the target damaged DNA base and the deoxyribose sugar to remove an alkylated base, leaving an apyrimidinic or apurinic site.

name: DNA-(apurinic or apyrimidinic site) lyase activity
description: Catalysis of the cleavage of the C-O-P bond 3' to the apurinic or apyrimidinic site in DNA by a beta-elimination reaction, leaving a 3'-terminal unsaturated sugar and a product with a terminal 5'-phosphate.

name: positive regulation of thyroid hormone generation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of thyroid hormone generation.

name: regulation of thyroid-stimulating hormone secretion
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of thyroid-stimulating hormone secretion.

name: methylated-DNA-[protein]-cysteine S-methyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: DNA (containing 6-O-methylguanine) + (protein)-L-cysteine = DNA (without 6-O-methylguanine) + protein S-methyl-L-cysteine.

name: positive regulation of flagellated sperm motility
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of flagellated sperm motility.

name: DNA ligase activity
description: Catalysis of the formation of a phosphodiester bond between the 3'-hydroxyl group at the end of one DNA chain and the 5'-phosphate group at the end of another. This reaction requires an energy source such as ATP or NAD+.

name: DNA ligase (ATP) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + deoxyribonucleotide(n) + deoxyribonucleotide(m) = AMP + diphosphate + deoxyribonucleotide(n+m).

name: DNA nucleotidylexotransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: deoxynucleoside triphosphate + DNA(n) = diphosphate + DNA(n+1).

name: DNA photolyase activity
description: Catalysis of the repair of a photoproduct resulting from ultraviolet irradiation of two adjacent pyrimidine residues in DNA.

name: positive regulation of miRNA catabolic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of miRNA catabolic process.

name: positive regulation of histone H4-K16 acetylation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of histone H4-K16 acetylation.

name: DNA topoisomerase activity
description: Catalysis of the transient cleavage and passage of individual DNA strands or double helices through one another, resulting a topological transformation in double-stranded DNA.

name: DNA topoisomerase type I activity
description: Catalysis of a DNA topological transformation by transiently cleaving one DNA strand at a time to allow passage of another strand; changes the linking number by +1 per catalytic cycle.

name: DNA topoisomerase type II (ATP-hydrolyzing) activity
description: Catalysis of a DNA topological transformation by transiently cleaving a pair of complementary DNA strands to form a gate through which a second double-stranded DNA segment is passed, after which the severed strands in the first DNA segment are rejoined; product release is coupled to ATP binding and hydrolysis; changes the linking number in multiples of 2.

name: negative regulation of nuclear-transcribed mRNA catabolic process, nonsense-mediated decay
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of nuclear-transcribed mRNA catabolic process, nonsense-mediated decay.

name: FMN adenylyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + FMN = diphosphate + FAD.

name: age-dependent response to oxidative stress
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of oxidative stress, a state often resulting from exposure to high levels of reactive oxygen species, where the change varies according to the age of the cell or organism.

name: replicative cell aging
description: The process associated with progression of the cell from its inception to the end of its lifespan that occurs as the cell continues cycles of growth and division.

name: chronological cell aging
description: The process associated with progression of the cell from its inception to the end of its lifespan that occurs when the cell is in a non-dividing, or quiescent, state.

name: RNA ligase (ATP) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + ribonucleotide(n) + ribonucleotide(m) = AMP + diphosphate + ribonucleotide(n+m).

name: negative regulation of SREBP signaling pathway
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the SREBP signaling pathway.

name: RNA-3'-phosphate cyclase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + RNA 3'-terminal-phosphate = AMP + diphosphate + RNA terminal-2',3'-cyclic-phosphate.

name: RNA-directed DNA polymerase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: deoxynucleoside triphosphate + DNA(n) = diphosphate + DNA(n+1). Catalyzes RNA-template-directed extension of the 3'- end of a DNA strand by one deoxynucleotide at a time.

name: regulation of germinal center formation
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of germinal center formation.

name: negative regulation of germinal center formation
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of germinal center formation.

name: positive regulation of germinal center formation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of germinal center formation.

name: regulation of immunoglobulin production
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of immunoglobulin production.

name: RNA-directed 5'-3' RNA polymerase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: nucleoside triphosphate + RNA(n) = diphosphate + RNA(n+1); uses an RNA template, i.e. the catalysis of RNA-template-directed extension of the 3'-end of an RNA strand by one nucleotide at a time.

name: positive regulation of gene silencing by miRNA
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of gene silencing by miRNA.

name: nucleobase-containing small molecule interconversion
description: The chemical reactions and pathways by which a nucleobase, nucleoside or nucleotide small molecule is synthesized from another nucleobase, nucleoside or nucleotide small molecule.

name: positive regulation of immunoglobulin production
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of immunoglobulin production.

name: negative regulation of pre-miRNA processing
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of pre-microRNA processing.

name: formate metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving formate, also known as methanoate, the anion HCOO- derived from methanoic (formic) acid.

name: positive regulation of miRNA metabolic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of miRNA metabolic process.

name: 18S rRNA (adenine(1779)-N(6)/adenine(1780)-N(6))-dimethyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 4 S-adenosyl-L-methionine + adenine(1779)/adenine(1780) in 18S rRNA = 4 S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + N(6)-dimethyladenine(1779)/N(6)-dimethyladenine(1780) in 18S rRNA.

name: tRNA (guanine(37)-N(1))-methyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + guanine(37) in tRNA = N(1)-methylguanine(37) in tRNA + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.

name: age-dependent response to reactive oxygen species
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of reactive oxygen species, where the change varies according to the age of the cell or organism.

name: UDP-glucose:glycoprotein glucosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the addition of UDP-glucose on to asparagine-linked (N-linked) oligosaccharides of the form Man7-9GlcNAc2 on incorrectly folded glycoproteins.

name: positive regulation of tolerance induction to self antigen
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of tolerance induction to self antigen.

name: UTP:glucose-1-phosphate uridylyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: alpha-D-glucose 1-phosphate + UTP = diphosphate + UDP-D-glucose.

name: positive regulation of immunoglobulin biosynthetic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of immunoglobulin biosynthesis.

name: (S)-2-hydroxy-acid oxidase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-2-hydroxy-acid + O2 = 2-oxo acid + hydrogen peroxide.

name: UDP-N-acetylglucosamine-dolichyl-phosphate N-acetylglucosaminephosphotransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + dolichyl phosphate = UMP + N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-diphosphodolichol.

name: UDP-N-acetylglucosamine-lysosomal-enzyme N-acetylglucosaminephosphotransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + lysosomal-enzyme D-mannose = UMP + lysosomal-enzyme N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-phospho-D-mannose.

name: UDP-N-acetylglucosamine diphosphorylase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine 1-phosphate + UTP = diphosphate + UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine.

name: UDP-glucose 4-epimerase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-glucose = UDP-galactose.

name: negative regulation of stem cell proliferation
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of stem cell proliferation.

name: positive regulation of stem cell proliferation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of stem cell proliferation.

name: UDP-glucose 6-dehydrogenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + 2 NAD(+) + UDP-alpha-D-glucose = 3 H(+) + 2 NADH + UDP-alpha-D-glucuronate.

name: regulation of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity.

name: N1-acetylspermidine:oxygen oxidoreductase (3-acetamidopropanal-forming) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + N(1)-acetylspermidine + O(2) = 3-acetamidopropanal + H(2)O(2) + putrescine.

name: positive regulation of early endosome to late endosome transport
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of early endosome to late endosome transport.

name: spermidine:oxygen oxidoreductase (3-aminopropanal-forming) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + O(2) + spermidine = 3-aminopropanal + H(2)O(2) + putrescine.

name: negative regulation of receptor catabolic process
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of receptor catabolic process.

name: N1-acetylspermine:oxygen oxidoreductase (3-acetamidopropanal-forming) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + N(1)-acetylspermine + O(2) = 3-acetamidopropanal + H(2)O(2) + spermidine.

name: spermine:oxygen oxidoreductase (spermidine-forming) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + O(2) + spermine = 3-aminopropanal + H(2)O(2) + spermidine.

name: regulation of early endosome to late endosome transport
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of early endosome to late endosome transport.

name: dol-P-Man:Man(7)GlcNAc(2)-PP-Dol alpha-1,6-mannosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: alpha-D-man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-(alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6))-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + dolichyl D-mannosyl phosphate = H(+) + alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-(alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-(alpha-D-Man-(1->6))-alpha-D-Man-(1->6))-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + dolichyl phosphate.

name: dol-P-Man:Man(8)GlcNAc(2)-PP-Dol alpha-1,2-mannosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: alpha-D-man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-(alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-(alpha-D-Man-(1->6))-alpha-D-Man-(1->6))-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + dolichyl D-mannosyl phosphate = H(+) + alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-(alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6))-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + dolichyl phosphate.

name: NAD+ ADP-ribosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NAD+ + (ADP-D-ribosyl)(n)-acceptor = nicotinamide + (ADP-D-ribosyl)(n+1)-acceptor.

name: L-iduronidase activity
description: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of alpha-L-iduronosidic linkages in dermatan sulfate.

name: L-serine ammonia-lyase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: L-serine = pyruvate + NH3.

name: N-acetylgalactosamine-4-sulfatase activity
description: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the 4-sulfate groups of the N-acetyl-D-galactosamine 4-sulfate units of chondroitin sulfate and dermatan sulfate.

name: N-acetylglucosamine-1-phosphodiester alpha-N-acetylglucosaminidase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: glycoprotein N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-phospho-D-mannose + H2O = N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + glycoprotein phospho-D-mannose.

name: negative regulation of apolipoprotein binding
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of apolipoprotein binding.

name: N-acetyllactosamine synthase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-galactose + N-acetyl-D-glucosamine = UDP + N-acetyllactosamine.

name: fucosidase activity
description: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of fucosyl compounds, substances containing a group derived from a cyclic form of fucose or a fucose derivative.

name: regulation of interleukin-1-mediated signaling pathway
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of interleukin-1-mediated signaling pathway.

name: (N-acetylneuraminyl)-galactosylglucosylceramide N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine + (N-acetylneuraminyl)-D-galactosyl-D-glucosylceramide = UDP + N-acetyl-D-galactosaminyl-(N-acetylneuraminyl)-D-galactosyl-D-glucosylceramide.

name: N4-(beta-N-acetylglucosaminyl)-L-asparaginase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: N(4)-(beta-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl)-L-asparagine + H(2)O = N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminylamine + L-aspartate + H(+).

name: glucosidase activity
description: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of glucosyl compounds, substances containing a group derived from a cyclic form of glucose or a glucose derivative.

name: regulation of genetic imprinting
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of genetic imprinting.

name: negative regulation of cellular response to testosterone stimulus
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cellular response to testosterone stimulus.

name: mannosidase activity
description: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of mannosyl compounds, substances containing a group derived from a cyclic form of mannose or a mannose derivative.

name: negative regulation of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity.

name: lipopolysaccharide transport
description: The directed movement of lipopolysaccharides into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. A lipopolysaccharide is any of a group of related, structurally complex components of the outer membrane of Gram-negative bacteria. Lipopolysaccharides consist three covalently linked regions, lipid A, core oligosaccharide, and an O side chain. Lipid A is responsible for the toxicity of the lipopolysaccharide.

name: positive regulation of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity.

name: positive regulation of dendritic cell apoptotic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of dendritic cell apoptotic process.

name: CTP:3'-cytidine-tRNA cytidylyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: a tRNA with a 3' cytidine + CTP = a tRNA with a 3' CC end + diphosphate.

name: ATP:3'-cytidine-cytidine-tRNA adenylyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: a tRNA with a 3' CC end + ATP = a tRNA with a 3' CCA end + diphosphate.

name: NADPH:quinone reductase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NADPH + H+ + quinone = NADP+ + semiquinone.

name: NAD+ kinase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + NAD(+) = ADP + 2 H(+) + NADP(+).

name: NAD+ synthase (glutamine-hydrolyzing) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + deamido-NAD+ + L-glutamine + H2O = AMP + diphosphate + NAD+ + L-glutamate.

name: NAD+ nucleosidase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NAD+ + H2O = nicotinamide + ADP-ribose.

name: NADH dehydrogenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NADH + H+ + acceptor = NAD+ + reduced acceptor.

name: NAD(P)H dehydrogenase (quinone) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NAD(P)H + H+ + a quinone = NAD(P)+ + a hydroquinone.

name: NAD(P)+-protein-arginine ADP-ribosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NAD(P)+ + L-arginine = nicotinamide + N2-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-arginine.

name: negative regulation of dendritic cell apoptotic process
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of dendritic cell apoptotic process.

name: NAD(P)+ transhydrogenase (B-specific) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NADPH + H+ + NAD+ = NADP+ + NADH + H+, driving the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other. In the course of the reaction (left to right) one H atom is transferred from inside the cell to outside. The reaction is B-specific (i.e. the pro-S hydrogen is transferred from the 4-position of reduced nicotinamide cofactor) with respect to both NAD+ and NADP+.

name: pantothenate metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving pantothenate, the anion of pantothenic acid, the amide of beta-alanine and pantoic acid. It is a B complex vitamin that is a constituent of coenzyme A and is distributed ubiquitously in foods.

name: NADPH-hemoprotein reductase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NADPH + H+ + n oxidized hemoprotein = NADP+ + n reduced hemoprotein.

name: coenzyme A catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of coenzyme A, 3'-phosphoadenosine-(5')diphospho(4')pantatheine, an acyl carrier in many acylation and acyl-transfer reactions in which the intermediate is a thiol ester.

name: coenzyme A biosynthetic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of coenzyme A, 3'-phosphoadenosine-(5')diphospho(4')pantatheine, an acyl carrier in many acylation and acyl-transfer reactions in which the intermediate is a thiol ester.

name: dol-P-Man:Man(6)GlcNAc(2)-PP-Dol alpha-1,2-mannosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: alpha-D-man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-(alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6))-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + dolichyl D-mannosyl phosphate = H(+) + alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-(alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6))-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + dolichyl phosphate.

name: positive regulation of interleukin-5 secretion
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of interleukin-5 secretion.

name: coenzyme A metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving coenzyme A, 3'-phosphoadenosine-(5')diphospho(4')pantatheine, an acyl carrier in many acylation and acyl-transfer reactions in which the intermediate is a thiol ester.

name: CTP:tRNA cytidylyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: a tRNA precursor + CTP = a tRNA with a 3' cytidine end + diphosphate.

name: small ribosomal subunit
description: The smaller of the two subunits of a ribosome.

name: negative regulation of interleukin-13 secretion
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of interleukin-13 secretion.

name: large ribosomal subunit
description: The larger of the two subunits of a ribosome. Two sites on the ribosomal large subunit are involved in translation, namely the aminoacyl site (A site) and peptidyl site (P site).

name: dol-P-Man:Man(5)GlcNAc(2)-PP-Dol alpha-1,3-mannosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: an alpha-D-man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-(alpha-D-Man-(1->6))-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + dolichyl D-mannosyl phosphate = H(+) + alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-(alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6))-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + dolichyl phosphate.

name: positive regulation of interleukin-13 secretion
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of interleukin-13 secretion.

name: negative regulation of interleukin-1-mediated signaling pathway
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of interleukin-1-mediated signaling pathway.

name: glutamate synthase activity
description: Catalysis of the formation of L-glutamine and 2-oxoglutarate from L-glutamate, using NADH, NADPH or ferredoxin as hydrogen acceptors.

name: negative regulation of interleukin-5 secretion
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of interleukin-5 secretion.

name: chlorophyll biosynthetic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of chlorophyll, any compound of magnesium complexed in a porphyrin (tetrapyrrole) ring and which functions as a photosynthetic pigment, from less complex precursors.

name: molecular hydrogen transport
description: The directed movement of molecular hydrogen (H2) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

name: regulation of rubidium ion transport
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of rubidium ion transport.

name: proton transport
description: The directed movement of protons (hydrogen ions) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

name: ATP hydrolysis coupled proton transport
description: The transport of protons against an electrochemical gradient, using energy from ATP hydrolysis.

name: regulation of mitotic recombination
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of DNA recombination during mitosis.

name: regulation of DNA recombination
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of DNA recombination, a DNA metabolic process in which a new genotype is formed by reassortment of genes resulting in gene combinations different from those that were present in the parents.

name: lactase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: lactose + H2O = D-glucose + D-galactose.

name: regulation of immune system process
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of an immune system process.

name: phosphopyruvate hydratase complex
description: A multimeric enzyme complex, usually a dimer or an octamer, that catalyzes the conversion of 2-phospho-D-glycerate to phosphoenolpyruvate and water.

name: negative regulation of immune system process
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of an immune system process.

name: single-stranded DNA endodeoxyribonuclease activity
description: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of ester linkages within a single-stranded deoxyribonucleic acid molecule by creating internal breaks.

name: positive regulation of immune system process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of an immune system process.

name: regulation of leukocyte migration
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte migration.

name: maltose metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the disaccharide maltose (4-O-alpha-D-glucopyranosyl-D-glucopyranose), an intermediate in the catabolism of glycogen and starch.

name: positive regulation of acute inflammatory response
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of an acute inflammatory response.

name: mitotic spindle elongation
description: The cell cycle process in which the distance is lengthened between poles of the mitotic spindle. Mitotic spindle elongation begins during mitotic prophase and ends during mitotic anaphase B.

name: negative regulation of chronic inflammatory response
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of a chronic inflammatory response.

name: positive regulation of chronic inflammatory response
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of a chronic inflammatory response.

name: respiratory burst involved in defense response
description: A phase of elevated metabolic activity, during which oxygen consumption increases made as part of a defense response ; this leads to the production, by an NADH dependent system, of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2), superoxide anions and hydroxyl radicals.

name: positive regulation of transcription regulatory region DNA binding
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription regulatory region DNA binding.

name: negative regulation of type B pancreatic cell apoptotic process
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of type B pancreatic cell apoptotic process.

name: positive regulation of type B pancreatic cell apoptotic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of type B pancreatic cell apoptotic process.

name: regulation of transcription regulatory region DNA binding
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription regulatory region DNA binding.

name: negative regulation of transcription regulatory region DNA binding
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of transcription regulatory region DNA binding.

name: negative regulation of motor neuron apoptotic process
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of motor neuron apoptotic process.

name: ATP synthesis coupled proton transport
description: The transport of protons across a membrane to generate an electrochemical gradient (proton-motive force) that powers ATP synthesis.

name: negative regulation of cardiac muscle cell myoblast differentiation
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle cell myoblast differentiation.

name: positive regulation of leukocyte chemotaxis
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte chemotaxis.

name: ribosomal small subunit assembly
description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of constituent RNAs and proteins to form the small ribosomal subunit.

name: positive regulation of cellular extravasation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of cellular extravasation.

name: alpha-1,2-mannosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the transfer of a mannose residue to an oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-(1->2) linkage.

name: negative regulation of leukocyte activation
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte activation.

name: negative regulation of leukocyte migration
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte migration.

name: alpha-1,3-mannosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the transfer of a mannose residue to an oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-(1->3) linkage.

name: positive regulation of leukocyte migration
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte migration.

name: negative regulation of leukocyte chemotaxis
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte chemotaxis.

name: mannosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the transfer of a mannosyl group to an acceptor molecule, typically another carbohydrate or a lipid.

name: positive regulation of rubidium ion transmembrane transporter activity
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of rubidium ion transmembrane transporter activity.

name: positive regulation of rubidium ion transport
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of rubidium ion transport.

name: regulation of cellular response to X-ray
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cellular response to X-ray.

name: chlorophyll catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of chlorophyll, any compound of magnesium complexed in a porphyrin (tetrapyrrole) ring and which functions as a photosynthetic pigment, into less complex products.

name: positive regulation of cellular response to X-ray
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cellular response to X-ray.

name: acetylcholinesterase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: acetylcholine + H2O = choline + acetate.

name: acid phosphatase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: an orthophosphoric monoester + H2O = an alcohol + phosphate, with an acid pH optimum.

name: positive regulation of B cell tolerance induction
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of B cell tolerance induction.

name: aconitate hydratase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: citrate = isocitrate. The reaction occurs in two steps: (1) citrate = cis-aconitate + H2O, (2) cis-aconitate + H2O = isocitrate. This reaction is the interconversion of citrate and isocitrate via the labile, enzyme-bound intermediate cis-aconitate. Water is removed from one part of the citrate molecule and added back to a different atom to form isocitrate.

name: acetyl-CoA C-acetyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 2 acetyl-CoA = CoA + acetoacetyl-CoA.

name: acetyl-CoA hydrolase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + H(2)O = acetate + CoA + H(+).

name: acetate-CoA ligase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + acetate + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + acetyl-CoA.

name: acetyl-CoA C-acyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: acyl-CoA + acetyl-CoA = CoA + 3-oxoacyl-CoA.

name: acetyl-CoA carboxylase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + acetyl-CoA + HCO3- = ADP + phosphate + malonyl-CoA.

name: diadenosine tetraphosphate biosynthetic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of diadenosine tetraphosphate, a derivative of the nucleoside adenosine with four phosphate groups attached.

name: regulation of epithelial cell differentiation involved in kidney development
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell differentiation involved in kidney development.

name: energy derivation by oxidation of organic compounds
description: The chemical reactions and pathways by which a cell derives energy from organic compounds; results in the oxidation of the compounds from which energy is released.

name: alpha-1,6-mannosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the transfer of a mannose residue to an oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-(1->6) linkage.

name: reproduction
description: The production of new individuals that contain some portion of genetic material inherited from one or more parent organisms.

name: mitochondrial genome maintenance
description: The maintenance of the structure and integrity of the mitochondrial genome; includes replication and segregation of the mitochondrial chromosome.

name: negative regulation of acute inflammatory response
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of an acute inflammatory response.

name: single strand break repair
description: The repair of single strand breaks in DNA. Repair of such breaks is mediated by the same enzyme systems as are used in base excision repair.

name: acyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: acyl-CoA + acceptor = 2,3-dehydroacyl-CoA + reduced acceptor.

name: acyl-CoA ligase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + a long-chain carboxylic acid + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + an acyl-CoA; long-chain fatty acids have chain lengths of C13 to C22.

name: trans-hexaprenyltranstransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: all-trans-hexaprenyl diphosphate + isopentenyl diphosphate = all-trans-heptaprenyl diphosphate + diphosphate.

name: positive regulation of T cell tolerance induction
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell tolerance induction.

name: acyl-CoA oxidase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: acyl-CoA + O2 = trans-2,3-dehydroacyl-CoA + hydrogen peroxide.

name: regulation of T cell anergy
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell anergy.

name: acylphosphatase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: an acyl phosphate + H2O = a carboxylate + phosphate.

name: negative regulation of T cell anergy
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell anergy.

name: adenine phosphoribosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: AMP + diphosphate = adenine + 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate.

name: positive regulation of T cell anergy
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell anergy.

name: photosynthesis
description: The synthesis by organisms of organic chemical compounds, especially carbohydrates, from carbon dioxide (CO2) using energy obtained from light rather than from the oxidation of chemical compounds.

name: negative regulation of cAMP-dependent protein kinase activity
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cAMP-dependent protein kinase activity.

name: positive regulation of cAMP-dependent protein kinase activity
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cAMP-dependent protein kinase activity.

name: regulation of interleukin-8 secretion
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of interleukin-8 secretion.

name: prostaglandin D2 11-ketoreductase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: prostaglandin D2 + H+ + NADPH -> 11-epi-prostaglandin F2alpha + NADP+.

name: 13-prostaglandin reductase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 15-keto-prostaglandin + NAD(P)H + H+ -> 13,14-dihydro-15-keto-prostaglandin + NAD(P)+. This reaction is the reduction of 15-keto-prostaglandin.

name: rRNA (adenine-N6,N6-)-dimethyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the dimethylation two adjacent A residues in the loop closing the 3'-terminal stem of the 18S rRNA, using S-adenosyl-L-methionine as a methyl donor.

name: exosome (RNase complex)
description: A ribonuclease complex that has 3-prime to 5-prime exoribonuclease activity and possibly endoribonuclease activity, producing 5-prime-phosphomonoesters. Participates in a multitude of cellular RNA processing and degradation events preventing nuclear export and/or translation of aberrant RNAs. Restricted to processing linear and circular single-stranded RNAs (ssRNA) only. RNAs with complex secondary structures may have to be unwound or pre-processed by co-factors prior to entering the complex, esp if the 3-prime end is structured.

name: inactivation of MAPK activity
description: Any process that terminates the activity of the active enzyme MAP kinase.

name: transforming growth factor beta binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with TGF-beta, transforming growth factor beta, a multifunctional peptide that controls proliferation, differentiation and other functions in many cell types.

name: activation of MAPK activity
description: The initiation of the activity of the inactive enzyme MAP kinase (MAPK).

name: actin crosslink formation
description: The process in which two or more actin filaments are connected together by proteins that act as crosslinks between the filaments. The crosslinked filaments may be on the same or differing axes.

name: activation of MAPKK activity
description: The initiation of the activity of the inactive enzyme MAP kinase kinase (MAPKK).

name: viral penetration into host nucleus
description: The crossing by the virus of the host nuclear membrane, either as naked viral genome or for small viruses as an intact capsid.

name: activation of MAPKKK activity
description: Any process that initiates the activity of the inactive enzyme MAP kinase kinase kinase (MAPKKK).

name: catecholamine secretion
description: The regulated release of catecholamines by a cell. The catecholamines are a group of physiologically important biogenic amines that possess a catechol (3,4-dihydroxyphenyl) nucleus and are derivatives of 3,4-dihydroxyphenylethylamine.

name: intracellular transport of virus
description: The directed movement of a virus, or part of a virus, within the host cell.

name: nuclear-transcribed mRNA catabolic process, nonsense-mediated decay
description: The nonsense-mediated decay pathway for nuclear-transcribed mRNAs degrades mRNAs in which an amino-acid codon has changed to a nonsense codon; this prevents the translation of such mRNAs into truncated, and potentially harmful, proteins.

name: chromatin silencing at rDNA
description: Repression of transcription of ribosomal DNA by altering the structure of chromatin.

name: rDNA binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with DNA sequences encoding ribosomal RNA.

name: positive regulation of metanephric glomerular visceral epithelial cell development
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of metanephric glomerular visceral epithelial cell development.

name: regulation of cAMP-dependent protein kinase activity
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cAMP-dependent protein kinase activity.

name: sperm flagellum
description: A microtubule-based flagellum (or cilium) that is part of a sperm, a mature male germ cell that develops from a spermatid.

name: beta-amyloid metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving beta-amyloid, a glycoprotein associated with Alzheimer's disease, and its precursor, amyloid precursor protein (APP).

name: positive regulation of hematopoietic stem cell migration
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of hematopoietic stem cell migration.

name: positive regulation of viral transcription
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of viral transcription.

name: regulation of opioid receptor signaling pathway
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of opioid receptor signaling pathway.

name: CatSper complex
description: A sperm-specific voltage-gated calcium channel that controls the intracellular calcium ion concentration and, thereby, the swimming behavior of sperm. Consists of a heteromeric tetramer surrounding a calcium ion- selective pore. May also contain additional auxiliary subunits.

name: BMP binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a member of the bone morphogenetic protein (BMP) family.

name: positive regulation of hepatic stellate cell activation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of hepatic stellate cell activation.

name: histone H3-K9 dimethylation
description: The modification of histone H3 by addition of two methyl groups to lysine at position 9 of the histone.

name: histone H3-K9 trimethylation
description: The modification of histone H3 by addition of three methyl groups to lysine at position 9 of the histone.

name: cellular response to platelet-derived growth factor stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a platelet-derived growth factor stimulus.

name: MAPK import into nucleus
description: The directed movement of a MAP kinase to the nucleus upon activation.

name: male germ-line stem cell asymmetric division
description: The self-renewing division of a germline stem cell in the male gonad, to produce a daughter stem cell and a daughter germ cell, which will divide to form the male gametes.

name: response to redox state
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating redox state. Redox state refers to the balance of oxidized versus reduced forms of electron donors and acceptors in an organelle, cell or organ; plastoquinone, glutathione (GSH/GSSG), and nicotinamide nucleotides (NAD+/NADH and NADP+/NADPH) are among the most important.

name: positive regulation of nitric-oxide synthase biosynthetic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a nitric oxide synthase enzyme.

name: negative regulation of nitric-oxide synthase biosynthetic process
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a nitric-oxide synthase enzyme.

name: response to platelet-derived growth factor
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a platelet-derived growth factor stimulus.

name: positive regulation of interleukin-8 secretion
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of interleukin-8 secretion.

name: hyaluranon cable
description: A cable structure, surrounding some cell types (e.g. proximal or bronchial tubular epithelial cells), and composed of hyaluranon (HA), a ubiquitous connective tissue glycosaminoglycan.

name: negative regulation of glutamine transport
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of glutamine transport.

name: very long-chain fatty-acyl-CoA metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving very long-chain fatty-acyl-CoAs, any derivative of coenzyme A in which the sulfhydryl group is in a thioester linkage with a medium-chain fatty-acyl group. A very long-chain fatty acid is a fatty acid which has a chain length greater than C22.

name: medium-chain fatty-acyl-CoA metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving medium-chain fatty-acyl-CoAs, any derivative of coenzyme A in which the sulfhydryl group is in a thioester linkage with a long-chain fatty-acyl group. A medium-chain fatty acid is a fatty acid with a chain length of between C6 and C12.

name: pancreas morphogenesis
description: Morphogenesis of the pancreas. Morphogenesis is the process in which anatomical structures are generated and organized.

name: protein phosphatase type 2A complex
description: A protein complex that has protein serine/threonine phosphatase activity that is polycation-stimulated (PCS), being directly stimulated by protamine, polylysine, or histone H1; it constitutes a subclass of several enzymes activated by different histones and polylysine, and consists of catalytic, scaffolding, and regulatory subunits. The catalytic and scaffolding subunits form the core enzyme, and the holoenzyme also includes the regulatory subunit.

name: lung proximal/distal axis specification
description: The establishment, maintenance and elaboration of the proximal/distal axis of the lung. The proximal/distal axis of the lung is defined by a line that runs from the trachea to the alveoli.

name: phosphorelay response regulator activity
description: Responds to a phosphorelay sensor to initiate a change in cell state or activity. The activity of the response regulator is regulated by transfer of a phosphate from a histidine residue in the sensor, to an aspartate residue in the response regulator. Many but not all response regulators act as transcriptional regulators to elicit a response.

name: nucleotide binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a nucleotide, any compound consisting of a nucleoside that is esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the ribose or deoxyribose.

name: fibroblast proliferation
description: The multiplication or reproduction of fibroblast cells, resulting in the expansion of the fibroblast population.

name: cob(II)alamin reductase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 2 cob(I)alamin + H(+) + NAD(+) = 2 cob(II)alamin + NADH.

name: MAPK cascade
description: An intracellular protein kinase cascade containing at least a MAPK, a MAPKK and a MAP3K. The cascade can also contain two additional tiers: the upstream MAP4K and the downstream MAP Kinase-activated kinase (MAPKAPK). The kinases in each tier phosphorylate and activate the kinases in the downstream tier to transmit a signal within a cell.

name: astrocyte activation
description: A change in morphology and behavior of an astrocyte resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor.

name: all-trans-retinol 13,14-reductase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: all-trans-13,14-dihydroretinol + A = all-trans-retinol + AH(2). Note that this reaction has only been observed to occur in the opposite direction.

name: protein phosphatase type 1 complex
description: A protein complex that possesses magnesium-dependent protein serine/threonine phosphatase (AMD phosphatase) activity, and consists of a catalytic subunit and one or more regulatory subunits that dictates the phosphatase's substrate specificity, function, and activity.

name: positive regulation of cell division
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell division.

name: behavioral response to cocaine
description: Any process that results in a change in the behavior of an organism as a result of a cocaine stimulus.

name: negative regulation of cell division
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell division.

name: negative regulation of fibroblast proliferation
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of multiplication or reproduction of fibroblast cells.

name: phosphorelay signal transduction system
description: A conserved series of molecular signals found in prokaryotes and eukaryotes; involves autophosphorylation of a histidine kinase and the transfer of the phosphate group to an aspartate that then acts as a phospho-donor to response regulator proteins.

name: positive regulation of fibroblast proliferation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of multiplication or reproduction of fibroblast cells.

name: regulation of fibroblast proliferation
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of multiplication or reproduction of fibroblast cells.

name: alpha-linolenic acid metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving alpha-linolenic acid, an unsaturated omega-6 fatty acid that has the molecular formula C18H32O2.

name: peroxisome membrane class-1 targeting sequence binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a class I peroxisomal membrane targeting sequence, any of several sequences of amino acids within a protein that can act as a signal for the localization of the protein into the peroxisome membrane in a PEX19-dependent manner.

name: ethanolamine-phosphate phospho-lyase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + phosphoethanolamine = acetaldehyde + NH(4)(+) + phosphate.

name: misfolded protein binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a misfolded protein.

name: response to misfolded protein
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a misfolded protein stimulus.

name: lung neuroendocrine cell differentiation
description: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuroendocrine cell of the lung epithelium.

name: leukotriene B4 catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of leukotriene B4, a leukotriene composed of (6Z,8E,10E,14Z)-eicosatetraenoic acid having (5S)- and (12R)-hydroxy substituents.

name: neuroendocrine cell differentiation
description: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of a neuroendocrine cell. A neuroendocrine cell is a cell that receives input form a neuron which controls the secretion of an endocrine substance.

name: stomach neuroendocrine cell differentiation
description: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuroendocrine cell of the stomach epithelium.

name: carotid body glomus cell differentiation
description: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of a glomus cell of the carotid body. The carotid body is a specialized chemosensory organ that helps respond to hypoxia.

name: seminal vesicle epithelium development
description: The progression of the seminal vesicle epithelium over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

name: behavioral response to ethanol
description: Any process that results in a change in the behavior of an organism as a result of an ethanol stimulus.

name: adrenal chromaffin cell differentiation
description: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of an adrenal chromaffin cell. An adrenal chromaffin cell is a neuroendocrine cell that stores epinephrine secretory vesicles.

name: negative regulation of stomach neuroendocrine cell differentiation
description: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the differentiation of a neuroendocrine cell in the stomach.

name: cytoplasmic exosome (RNase complex)
description: A ribonuclease complex that has 3-prime to 5-prime processive hydrolytic exoribonuclease activity producing 5-prime-phosphomonoesters. Participates in a multitude of cellular RNA processing and degradation events preventing nuclear export and/or translation of aberrant RNAs. Restricted to processing linear and circular single-stranded RNAs (ssRNA) only. RNAs with complex secondary structures may have to be unwound or pre-processed by co-factors prior to entering the complex, esp if the 3-prime end is structured.

name: nuclear exosome (RNase complex)
description: A ribonuclease complex that has 3-prime to 5-prime processive and distributive hydrolytic exoribonuclease activity and endoribonuclease activity, producing 5-prime-phosphomonoesters. Participates in a multitude of cellular RNA processing and degradation events preventing nuclear export and/or translation of aberrant RNAs. Restricted to processing linear and circular single-stranded RNAs (ssRNA) only. RNAs with complex secondary structures may have to be unwound or pre-processed by co-factors prior to entering the complex, esp if the 3-prime end is structured.

name: regulation of hair follicle development
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hair follicle development.

name: 3'-5'-exoribonuclease activity
description: Catalysis of the sequential cleavage of mononucleotides from a free 3' terminus of an RNA molecule.

name: positive regulation of catagen
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of catagen, the regression phase of the hair cycle.

name: inactivation of MAPK activity involved in osmosensory signaling pathway
description: Any process that terminates the activity of the active enzyme MAP kinase during osmolarity sensing.

name: medium-chain fatty acid biosynthetic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of any fatty acid with a chain length of between C6 and C12.

name: ribonuclease MRP complex
description: A ribonucleoprotein complex that contains an RNA molecule of the snoRNA family, and cleaves the rRNA precursor as part of rRNA transcript processing. It also has other roles: In S. cerevisiae it is involved in cell cycle-regulated degradation of daughter cell-specific mRNAs, while in mammalian cells it also enters the mitochondria and processes RNAs to create RNA primers for DNA replication.

name: medium-chain fatty acid catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of any fatty acid with a chain length of between C6 and C12.

name: ribonuclease MRP activity
description: Catalysis of the site-specific cleavage of RNA by a catalytic RNA-mediated mechanism; substrates include the A3 site in the ITS1 of pre-rRNA.

name: short-chain fatty acid biosynthetic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of fatty acids with a chain length of less than C6.

name: N-acetylneuraminate synthase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: phosphoenolpyruvate + N-acetyl-D-mannosamine + H2O = phosphate + N-acetylneuraminate.

name: sphingosine hydroxylase activity
description: Catalysis of the hydroxylation of sphingolipid long chain bases.

name: tau protein binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with tau protein. tau is a microtubule-associated protein, implicated in Alzheimer's disease, Down Syndrome and ALS.

name: medium-chain fatty acid metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving medium-chain fatty acids, any fatty acid with a chain length of between C6 and C12.

name: positive regulation of hair follicle development
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of hair follicle development.

name: negative regulation of hair follicle development
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of hair follicle development.

name: osteoclast maturation
description: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an osteoclast cell to attain its fully functional state. An osteoclast is a specialized phagocytic cell associated with the absorption and removal of the mineralized matrix of bone tissue, and which typically differentiates from monocytes.

name: germline cell cycle switching, mitotic to meiotic cell cycle
description: The process in which a germline cell switches cell cycle mode from mitotic to meiotic division.

name: protein de-ADP-ribosylation
description: The process of removing one or more ADP-ribose residues from a protein.

name: regulation of cell cycle
description: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of progression through the cell cycle.

name: NAD transporter activity
description: Enables the directed movement of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide into, out of or within a cell, or between cells; transport may be of either the oxidized form, NAD, or the reduced form, NADH.

name: protein phosphatase 2A binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the enzyme protein phosphatase 2A.

name: protein C-terminal methylesterase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: C-terminal protein amino acid methyl ester + H2O = protein amino acid + methanol.

name: polynucleotide 5'-hydroxyl-kinase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NTP + 5'-dephosphopolynucleotide = NDP + 5'-phosphopolynucleotide. The polynucleotide may be DNA or RNA.

name: [acetyl-CoA carboxylase] kinase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + [acetyl-CoA carboxylase] = ADP + [acetyl-CoA carboxylase] phosphate.

name: ATP-dependent polyribonucleotide 5'-hydroxyl-kinase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + 5'-dephospho-RNA = ADP + 5'-phospho-RNA.

name: inner dynein arm assembly
description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an axonemal dynein inner arm, an inner arm structure present on the outer doublet microtubules of ciliary and flagellar axonemes.

name: polydeoxyribonucleotide kinase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: NTP + 5'-dephospho-DNA = NDP + 5'-phospho-DNA.

name: acylglycerol acyl-chain remodeling
description: Remodeling the acyl chains of an acylglycerol, through sequential deacylation and re-acylation reactions, to generate an acylglycerol containing different types of fatty acid acyl chains.

name: outer dynein arm
description: Outer arm structure present on the outer doublet microtubules of ciliary and flagellar axonemes. Outer dynein arms contain 2-3 heavy chains, two or more intermediate chains and a cluster of 4-8 light chains. Inner and outer dynein arms have different functions in the generation of microtubule-based motility.

name: outer dynein arm assembly
description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an axonemal dynein outer arm, an outer arm structure present on the outer doublet microtubules of ciliary and flagellar axonemes.

name: phosphatidylcholine acyl-chain remodeling
description: Remodeling the acyl chains of phosphatidylcholine, through sequential deacylation and re-acylation reactions, to generate phosphatidylcholine containing different types of fatty acid acyl chains.

name: phosphatidylethanolamine acyl-chain remodeling
description: Remodeling the acyl chains of phosphatidylethanolamine, through sequential deacylation and re-acylation reactions, to generate phosphatidylethanolamine containing different types of fatty acid acyl chains.

name: phosphatidylserine acyl-chain remodeling
