description: Combining with a peptide and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein; promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit of a heterotrimeric G-protein complex.

name: taste receptor activity
description: Combining with soluble compounds to initiate a change in cell activity. These receptors are responsible for the sense of taste.

name: positive regulation of reciprocal meiotic recombination
description: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of recombination during meiosis. Reciprocal meiotic recombination is the cell cycle process in which double strand breaks are formed and repaired through a double Holliday junction intermediate.

name: regulation of chromatin assembly
description: Any process the modulates the frequency, rate or extent of chromatin assembly. Chromatin assembly is the assembly of DNA, histone proteins, and other associated proteins into chromatin structure, beginning with the formation of the basic unit, the nucleosome, followed by organization of the nucleosomes into higher order structures, ultimately giving rise to a complex organization of specific domains within the nucleus.

name: retina layer formation
description: The process in which the vertebrate retina is organized into three laminae: the outer nuclear layer (ONL), which contains photoreceptor nuclei; the inner nuclear layer (INL), which contains amacrine, bipolar and horizontal cells; and the retinal ganglion cell (RGC) layer. Between the inner and outer nuclear layers, the outer plexiform layer (OPL) contains connections between the photoreceptors and bipolar and horizontal cells. The inner plexiform layer (IPL) is positioned between the INL and the ganglion cell layer and contains the dendrites of RGCs and processes of bipolar and amacrine cells. Spanning all layers of the retina are the radially oriented Mueller glia.

name: positive regulation of circadian sleep/wake cycle, wakefulness
description: Any process that increases the frequency, or extent of the wakeful phase of the circadian sleep/wake cycle. The wakeful phase is the part of the circadian sleep/wake cycle where the organism is not asleep.

name: recombination hotspot binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a region in a genome which promotes recombination.

name: embryo development
description: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an embryo from its formation until the end of its embryonic life stage. The end of the embryonic stage is organism-specific. For example, for mammals, the process would begin with zygote formation and end with birth. For insects, the process would begin at zygote formation and end with larval hatching. For plant zygotic embryos, this would be from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. For plant vegetative embryos, this would be from the initial determination of the cell or group of cells to form an embryo until the point when the embryo becomes independent of the parent plant.

name: negative regulation of interleukin-6 biosynthetic process
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of interleukin-6.

name: positive regulation of interleukin-5 biosynthetic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of interleukin-5.

name: regulation of interleukin-6 biosynthetic process
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of interleukin-6.

name: reciprocal meiotic recombination
description: The cell cycle process in which double strand breaks are formed and repaired through a double Holliday junction intermediate. This results in the equal exchange of genetic material between non-sister chromatids in a pair of homologous chromosomes. These reciprocal recombinant products ensure the proper segregation of homologous chromosomes during meiosis I and create genetic diversity.

name: regulation of mitotic cell cycle, embryonic
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of replication and segregation of genetic material in the embryo.

name: Scrib-APC-beta-catenin complex
description: A protein complex that contains the Scribble protein (a cell polarity determinant), the tumor suppressor protein adenomatous polyposis coli (APC), and beta-catenin; may be involved in the control of cell proliferation.

name: embryo development ending in birth or egg hatching
description: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an embryo over time, from zygote formation until the end of the embryonic life stage. The end of the embryonic life stage is organism-specific and may be somewhat arbitrary; for mammals it is usually considered to be birth, for insects the hatching of the first instar larva from the eggshell.

name: post-embryonic development
description: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the organism over time, from the completion of embryonic development to the mature structure. See embryonic development.

name: synaptonemal complex assembly
description: The cell cycle process in which the synaptonemal complex is formed. This is a structure that holds paired chromosomes together during prophase I of meiosis and that promotes genetic recombination.

name: dTDP-glucose 4,6-dehydratase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: dTDP-glucose = dTDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose + H(2)O.

name: axis specification
description: The establishment, maintenance and elaboration of a pattern along a line or around a point.

name: [heparan sulfate]-glucosamine 3-sulfotransferase 1 activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phosphoadenylyl sulfate + [heparan sulfate]-glucosamine = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + [heparan sulfate]-glucosamine 3-sulfate. The [heparan sulfate]-glucosamine 3-sulfate has a substrate consensus sequence of Glc(N2S>NAc)+/-6S GlcA GlcN2S*+/-6S GlcA>IdoA+/-2S Glc(N2S/NAc)+/-6S.

name: positive regulation of interleukin-3 biosynthetic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of interleukin-3.

name: active induction of host immune response by virus
description: The intentional, virally-encoded stimulation of a host defense response to viral infection.

name: meiotic prophase II
description: The cell cycle phase which is the first stage of meiosis II and during which chromosomes condense and the two daughter centrioles and their asters migrate toward the poles of the cell.

name: glycogenin glucosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-glucose + glycogenin = UDP + glucosylglycogenin.

name: glycerate dehydrogenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-glycerate + NAD+ = hydroxypyruvate + NADH + H+.

name: histone-arginine N-methyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + (histone)-arginine = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + (histone)-N-methyl-arginine.

name: negative regulation of interleukin-4 biosynthetic process
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of interleukin-4.

name: positive regulation of interleukin-4 biosynthetic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of interleukin-4.

name: negative regulation of cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation
description: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of cell morphogenesis contributing to cell differentiation. Cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation is the change in form (cell shape and size) that occurs when relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells, tissues, or organs of the mature organism or some other relatively stable phase of the organism's life history.

name: isovaleryl-CoA dehydrogenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 3-methylbutanoyl-CoA + ETF = 3-methylbut-2-enoyl-CoA + reduced ETF.

name: DNA double-strand break processing involved in repair via single-strand annealing
description: The 5' to 3' exonucleolytic resection of the DNA at the site of the break to form a 3' single-strand DNA overhang that results in the repair of a double strand break via single-strand annealing.

name: palmitoyl-(protein) hydrolase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: palmitoyl-protein + H2O = palmitate + protein.

name: female meiotic division
description: A cell cycle process by which the cell nucleus divides as part of a meiotic cell cycle in the female germline.

name: male meiosis
description: A cell cycle process by which the cell nucleus divides as part of a meiotic cell cycle in the male germline.

name: male meiosis I
description: A cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through male meiosis I, the first meiotic division in the male germline.

name: pyridoxal kinase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + pyridoxal = ADP + pyridoxal 5'-phosphate.

name: female meiosis I
description: The cell cycle process in which the first meiotic division occurs in the female germline.

name: protein-tyrosine sulfotransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + protein tyrosine = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + protein tyrosine-O-sulfate.

name: positive regulation of interleukin-6 biosynthetic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of interleukin-6.

name: procollagen-lysine 5-dioxygenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: procollagen L-lysine + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = procollagen 5-hydroxy-L-lysine + succinate + CO2.

name: positive regulation of interleukin-8 biosynthetic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of interleukin-8.

name: regulation of interleukin-8 biosynthetic process
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of interleukin-8.

name: viral capsid secondary envelopment
description: The process in which a capsid acquires another membrane envelope, subsequent to acquiring an initial membrane envelope.

name: queuine tRNA-ribosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: tRNA guanine + queuine = tRNA queuine + guanine.

name: negative regulation of interleukin-8 biosynthetic process
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of interleukin-8.

name: benzaldehyde dehydrogenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: benzaldehyde + NAD(P)+ + H2O = benzoate + NAD(P)H + H+.

name: cholesterol O-acyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: acyl-CoA + cholesterol = a cholesterol ester + CoA.

name: phenanthrene-9,10-epoxide hydrolase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: phenanthrene-9,10-oxide + H2O = trans-9,10-dihydrodiolphenanthrene.

name: sodium-independent icosanoid transport
description: The directed, sodium-independent, movement of icosanoids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Icosanoids are unsaturated C20 fatty acids and skeletally related compounds.

name: positive regulation of nitric oxide biosynthetic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of nitric oxide.

name: 3'(2'),5'-bisphosphate nucleotidase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + H2O = adenosine 5'-phosphate + phosphate.

name: inositol-1,4,5-trisphosphate 3-kinase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 1D-myo-inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate + ATP = 1D-myo-inositol 1,3,4,5-tetrakisphosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).

name: endomitotic cell cycle
description: A mitotic cell cycle in which chromosomes are replicated and sister chromatids separate, but spindle formation, nuclear membrane breakdown and nuclear division do not occur, resulting in an increased number of chromosomes in the cell.

name: D-aspartate oxidase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: D-aspartate + H2O + O2 = oxaloacetate + NH3 + hydrogen peroxide.

name: regulation of granulocyte macrophage colony-stimulating factor biosynthetic process
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of granulocyte macrophage colony-stimulating factor.

name: CDP-diacylglycerol-glycerol-3-phosphate 3-phosphatidyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + CDP-diacylglycerol = 3-(3-sn-phosphatidyl)-sn-glycerol 1-phosphate + CMP + H(+).

name: viral budding
description: A viral process by which enveloped viruses acquire a host-derived membrane enriched in viral proteins to form their external envelope. The process starts when nucleocapsids, assembled or in the process of being built, induce formation of a membrane curvature in the host plasma or organelle membrane and wrap up in the forming bud. The process ends when the bud is eventually pinched off by membrane scission to release the enveloped particle into the lumenal or extracellular space.

name: phosphofructokinase activity
description: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a fructose substrate molecule.

name: 3-hydroxyisobutyrate dehydrogenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 3-hydroxy-2-methylpropanoate + NAD+ = 2-methyl-3-oxopropanoate + NADH + H+.

name: N-acetylglucosamine-6-sulfatase activity
description: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the 6-sulfate group of the N-acetyl-D-glucosamine 6-sulfate units of heparan sulfate and keratan sulfate.

name: N-acetylglucosamine-6-phosphate deacetylase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: N-acetyl-D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + H2O = D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + acetate.

name: regulation of nitric oxide biosynthetic process
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of nitric oxide.

name: positive regulation of granulocyte macrophage colony-stimulating factor biosynthetic process
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of granulocyte macrophage colony-stimulating factor.

name: GDP-mannose 4,6-dehydratase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: GDP-alpha-D-mannose = GDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-mannose + H(2)O.

name: nucleosome organization
description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of one or more nucleosomes.

name: regulation of macrophage chemotaxis
description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of macrophage chemotaxis. Macrophage chemotaxis is the movement of a macrophage in response to an external stimulus.

name: negative regulation of plasminogen activation
description: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of plasminogen activation. Plasminogen activation is the process in which plasminogen is processed to plasmin.

name: male germ-line sex determination
description: The determination of sex and sexual phenotype in a male organism's germ line.

name: positive regulation of macrophage chemotaxis
description: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of macrophage chemotaxis. Macrophage chemotaxis is the movement of a macrophage in response to an external stimulus.

name: negative regulation of cGMP-mediated signaling
description: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of cGMP-mediated signaling. cGMP-mediated signaling is a series of molecular signals in which a cell uses cyclic GMP to convert an extracellular signal into a response.

name: male somatic sex determination
description: The determination of sex and sexual phenotypes in a male organism's soma.

name: histone H3-K4 demethylation, trimethyl-H3-K4-specific
description: The modification of histone H3 by the removal of a methyl group from a trimetylated lysine at position 4 of the histone.

name: female somatic sex determination
description: The determination of sex and sexual phenotypes in a female organism's soma.

name: histone H3-K4 demethylation
description: The modification of histone H3 by the removal of a methyl group from lysine at position 4 of the histone.

name: basement membrane organization
description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the basement membrane.

name: DNA N-glycosylase activity
description: Catalysis of the removal of damaged bases by cleaving the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the target damaged DNA base and the deoxyribose sugar. The reaction releases a free base and leaves an apurinic/apyrimidinic (AP) site.

name: positive regulation of plasminogen activation
description: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of plasminogen activation. Plasminogen activation is the process in which plasminogen is processed to plasmin.

name: pyrimidine nucleotide binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with pyrimidine nucleotide, any compound consisting of a pyrimidine nucleoside esterified with (ortho)phosphate.

name: DNA replication-dependent nucleosome disassembly
description: The controlled breakdown of nucleosomes on newly replicated DNA, coupled to strand elongation.

name: regulation of cGMP-mediated signaling
description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of cGMP-mediated signaling. cGMP-mediated signaling is a series of molecular signals in which a cell uses cyclic GMP to convert an extracellular signal into a response.

name: ER-associated misfolded protein catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of misfolded proteins transported from the endoplasmic reticulum and targeted to cytoplasmic proteasomes for degradation.

name: myristoyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the transfer of a myristoyl (CH3-[CH2]12-CO-) group to an acceptor molecule.

name: negative regulation of nitric oxide mediated signal transduction
description: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of nitric oxide mediated signal transduction. Nitric oxide mediated signal transduction is a series of molecular signals mediated by the detection of nitric oxide (NO).

name: gamma-glutamyl-peptidase activity
description: Catalysis of the cleavage of a gamma-linked glutamate bond.

name: positive regulation of cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation
description: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell morphogenesis contributing to cell differentiation. Cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation is the change in form (cell shape and size) that occurs when relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells, tissues, or organs of the mature organism or some other relatively stable phase of the organism's life history.

name: RNA ligase activity
description: Catalysis of the formation of a phosphodiester bond between a hydroxyl group at the end of one RNA chain and the 5'-phosphate group at the end of another.

name: membrane assembly
description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a membrane.

name: alpha-N-acetylgalactosaminidase activity
description: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal non-reducing N-acetyl-D-galactosamine residues in N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminides.

name: alpha-1,6-mannosylglycoprotein 2-beta-N-acetylglucosaminyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + alpha-D-mannosyl-1,6-(N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,3)-beta-D-mannosyl-R = UDP + N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,6-(N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,3)-beta-D-mannosyl-R.

name: regulation of asymmetric cell division
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of asymmetric cell division.

name: alpha-1,3-mannosylglycoprotein 4-beta-N-acetylglucosaminyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + (N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,3-(beta-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,6)-beta-D-mannosyl-R = UDP + N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,4-(N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1,2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,3-(beta-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,6)-beta-D-mannosyl-R.

name: blue light signaling pathway
description: The series of molecular signals initiated upon sensing of blue light by photoreceptor molecule, at a wavelength between 400nm and 470nm.

name: alanine-glyoxylate transaminase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: L-alanine + glyoxylate = pyruvate + glycine.

name: meiotic prophase I
description: The cell cycle phase which is the first stage of meiosis I and during which chromosomes condense and the two daughter centrioles and their asters migrate toward the poles of the cell.

name: synapsis
description: The meiotic cell cycle process where side by side pairing and physical juxtaposition of homologous chromosomes is created during meiotic prophase. Synapsis begins when the chromosome arms begin to pair from the clustered telomeres and ends when synaptonemal complex or linear element assembly is complete.

name: chondroitin 6-sulfotransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + chondroitin = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + chondroitin 6'-sulfate.

name: meiotic nuclear division
description: One of the two nuclear divisions that occur as part of the meiotic cell cycle.

name: carnitine O-octanoyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-carnitine + octanoyl-CoA = (S)-octanoylcarnitine + CoA.

name: positive regulation of abscisic acid-activated signaling pathway
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of abscisic acid (ABA) signaling.

name: meiosis I
description: The first meiotic nuclear division in which homologous chromosomes are paired and segregated from each other, producing two haploid daughter nuclei.

name: beta-galactosyl-N-acetylglucosaminylgalactosylglucosyl-ceramide beta-1,3-acetylglucosaminyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-beta-D-glucosylceramide = UDP + N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-beta-D-glucosylceramide.

name: regulation of cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell morphogenesis contributing to cell differentiation. Cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation is the change in form (cell shape and size) that occurs when relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells, tissues, or organs of the mature organism or some other relatively stable phase of the organism's life history.

name: negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to UV-induced DNA damage
description: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a UV damage stimulus.

name: development involved in symbiotic interaction
description: The progression of an organism from an initial condition to a later condition, occurring when the organism is in a symbiotic interaction.

name: positive regulation of sodium ion transport
description: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of sodium ions (Na+) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

name: negative regulation of fibroblast migration
description: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of fibroblast cell migration. Fibroblast cell migration is accomplished by extension and retraction of a pseudopodium.

name: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to UV-induced DNA damage
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a UV damage stimulus.

name: negative regulation of sodium ion transport
description: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of sodium ions (Na+) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

name: fibroblast migration
description: Cell migration that is accomplished by extension and retraction of a fibroblast pseudopodium. A fibroblast is a connective tissue cell which secretes an extracellular matrix rich in collagen and other macromolecules.

name: type III transforming growth factor beta receptor binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a type III transforming growth factor beta receptor.

name: negative regulation of macrophage chemotaxis
description: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of macrophage chemotaxis. Macrophage chemotaxis is the movement of a macrophage in response to an external stimulus.

name: type I transforming growth factor beta receptor binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a type I transforming growth factor beta receptor.

name: positive regulation of fibroblast migration
description: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of fibroblast cell migration. Fibroblast cell migration is accomplished by extension and retraction of a pseudopodium.

name: regulation of fibroblast migration
description: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of fibroblast cell migration. Fibroblast cell migration is accomplished by extension and retraction of a pseudopodium.

name: inhibin binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an inhibin monomer, any of the polypeptides that combine to form activin and inhibin dimers.

name: activation of transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase activity
description: Any process that initiates the activity of the inactive transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase activity.

name: signal complex assembly
description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a complex capable of relaying a signal within a cell.

name: negative regulation of epidermal growth factor-activated receptor activity
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of EGF-activated receptor activity.

name: regulation of epidermal growth factor-activated receptor activity
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of EGF-activated receptor activity.

name: epidermal growth factor receptor signaling pathway
description: A series of molecular signals initiated by binding of a ligand to the tyrosine kinase receptor EGFR (ERBB1) on the surface of a cell. The pathway ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: epidermal growth factor catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of epidermal growth factor (EGF), following internalization of the receptor-bound ligand into the signal-receiving cell. Full breakdown of epidermal growth factor results in a ligand that is unable to bind and activate its receptor.

name: transforming growth factor beta receptor signaling pathway
description: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of an extracellular ligand to a transforming growth factor beta receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: transmembrane receptor protein serine/threonine kinase signaling pathway
description: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of an extracellular ligand to a receptor on the surface of the target cell where the receptor possesses serine/threonine kinase activity, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: trans-2-enoyl-CoA reductase (NADPH) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: acyl-CoA + NADP+ = trans-2,3-dehydroacyl-CoA + NADPH + H+.

name: dense core granule membrane
description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a dense core granule.

name: common-partner SMAD protein phosphorylation
description: The process of introducing a phosphate group on to a common-partner SMAD protein. A common partner SMAD protein binds to pathway-restricted SMAD proteins forming a complex that translocates to the nucleus.

name: SMAD protein complex assembly
description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a protein complex that contains SMAD proteins.

name: CDP biosynthetic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of CDP, cytidine (5'-)diphosphate.

name: transforming growth factor beta receptor complex assembly
description: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a ligand-bound type II transforming growth factor beta (TGF-beta) receptor dimer with a type I TGF-beta receptor dimer, following ligand binding, to form a heterotetrameric TGF-beta receptor complex.

name: G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway
description: A series of molecular signals that proceeds with an activated receptor promoting the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha-subunit of an associated heterotrimeric G-protein complex. The GTP-bound activated alpha-G-protein then dissociates from the beta- and gamma-subunits to further transmit the signal within the cell. The pathway begins with receptor-ligand interaction, or for basal GPCR signaling the pathway begins with the receptor activating its G protein in the absence of an agonist, and ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.  The pathway can start from the plasma membrane, Golgi or nuclear membrane (PMID:24568158 and PMID:16902576).

name: G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway, coupled to cyclic nucleotide second messenger
description: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a G-protein coupled receptor binding to its physiological ligand, where the pathway proceeds with activation or inhibition of a nucleotide cyclase activity and a subsequent change in the concentration of a cyclic nucleotide.

name: SMAD protein import into nucleus
description: The directed movement of a SMAD proteins from the cytoplasm into the nucleus. Pathway-restricted SMAD proteins and common-partner SMAD proteins are involved in the transforming growth factor beta receptor signaling pathways.

name: IDP catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of IDP, inosine 5'-diphosphate.

name: transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine phosphatase signaling pathway
description: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of an extracellular ligand to a receptor on the surface of the target cell where the receptor possesses protein tyrosine phosphatase activity, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: adenylate cyclase-modulating G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway
description: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a G-protein coupled receptor binding to its physiological ligand, where the pathway proceeds through activation or inhibition of adenylyl cyclase activity and a subsequent change in the concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP).

name: adenylate cyclase-activating G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway
description: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a G-protein coupled receptor binding to its physiological ligand, where the pathway proceeds through activation of adenylyl cyclase activity and a subsequent increase in the concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP).

name: natural killer cell lectin-like receptor binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a lectin-like natural killer cell receptor.

name: sequestering of zinc ion
description: The process of binding or confining zinc ions such that they are separated from other components of a biological system.

name: protein-disulfide reductase (glutathione) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 2 glutathione + protein-disulfide = oxidized glutathione + protein-dithiol.

name: response to histamine
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a histamine stimulus. Histamine, the biogenic amine 2-(1H-imidazol-4-yl)ethanamine, is involved in local immune responses as well as regulating physiological function in the gut and acting as a neurotransmitter.

name: secretory granule lumen
description: The volume enclosed by the membrane of a secretory granule.

name: mannokinase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + D-mannose = ADP + D-mannose 6-phosphate.

name: histone H4-K20 trimethylation
description: The modification of histone H4 by addition of three methyl groups to lysine at position 20 of the histone.

name: SMC loading complex
description: A protein complex required for the loading of a structural maintenance of chromosome (SMC) complex, such as cohesin, condensin or SMC5/SMC6, onto DNA. Appears to be eukaryotically conserved.

name: sphinganine kinase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + sphinganine = ADP + sphinganine 1-phosphate.

name: viral entry into host cell
description: The process that occurs after viral attachment by which a virus, or viral nucleic acid, breaches the plasma membrane or cell envelope and enters the host cell. The process ends when the viral nucleic acid is released into the host cell cytoplasm.

name: sarcosine dehydrogenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: sarcosine + H2O + electron-transfer flavoprotein = glycine + formaldehyde + reduced electron-transfer flavoprotein.

name: muscle cell cellular homeostasis
description: The cellular homeostatic process that preserves a muscle cell in a stable functional or structural state.

name: acid secretion
description: The controlled release of acid by a cell or a tissue.

name: cell communication
description: Any process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

name: sulfuric ester hydrolase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: RSO-R' + H2O = RSOOH + R'H. This reaction is the hydrolysis of any sulfuric ester bond, any ester formed from sulfuric acid, O=SO(OH)2.

name: transaminase activity
description: Catalysis of the transfer of an amino group to an acceptor, usually a 2-oxo acid.

name: histone H4-K20 methylation
description: The modification of histone H4 by addition of one or more methyl groups to lysine at position 20 of the histone.

name: sulfite oxidase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: H(2)O + O(2) + sulfite = H(2)O(2) + H(+) + sulfate.

name: heterophilic cell-cell adhesion via plasma membrane cell adhesion molecules
description: The attachment of an adhesion molecule in one cell to a nonidentical adhesion molecule in an adjacent cell.

name: UDP-galactose:glucosylceramide beta-1,4-galactosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-D-galactose + a glucosylceramide = a lactosylceramide + uridine-5'-diphosphate. The glucosylceramide has sphinganine as the long chain base.

name: neuron cell-cell adhesion
description: The attachment of a neuron to another cell via adhesion molecules.

name: gamma-glutamyl carboxylase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: peptidyl-glutamate + reduced vitamin K + CO2 + O2 = peptidyl-gamma-carboxyglutamate + vitamin K epoxide.

name: GDP biosynthetic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of GDP, guanosine 5'-diphosphate.

name: cell adhesion
description: The attachment of a cell, either to another cell or to an underlying substrate such as the extracellular matrix, via cell adhesion molecules.

name: homophilic cell adhesion via plasma membrane adhesion molecules
description: The attachment of a plasma membrane adhesion molecule in one cell to an identical molecule in an adjacent cell.

name: diphosphoinositol-polyphosphate diphosphatase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: diphospho-myo-inositol polyphosphate + H2O = myo-inositol polyphosphate + phosphate.

name: borate transmembrane transporter activity
description: Enables the transport of borate across a membrane against the concentration gradient.

name: leukocyte cell-cell adhesion
description: The attachment of a leukocyte to another cell via adhesion molecules.

name: borate transport
description: The directed movement of borate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Borate is the anion (BO3)3-; boron is a group 13 element, with properties which are borderline between metals and non-metals.

name: ADP-sugar diphosphatase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ADP-sugar + H2O = AMP + sugar 1-phosphate.

name: regulation of ion transmembrane transport
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

name: aminobutyraldehyde dehydrogenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: 4-aminobutanal + NAD+ + H2O = 4-aminobutanoate + NADH + 2 H+.

name: positive regulation of appetite
description: Any process that increases appetite.

name: basement membrane disassembly
description: The controlled breakdown of the basement membrane in the context of a normal process such as imaginal disc eversion.

name: regulation of mRNA export from nucleus
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of mRNA from the nucleus to the cytoplasm.

name: positive regulation of ion transmembrane transport
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

name: negative regulation of ion transmembrane transport
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

name: cell-matrix adhesion
description: The binding of a cell to the extracellular matrix via adhesion molecules.

name: calcium-independent cell-matrix adhesion
description: The binding of a cell to the extracellular matrix via adhesion molecules that do not require the presence of calcium for the interaction.

name: signal transduction
description: The cellular process in which a signal is conveyed to trigger a change in the activity or state of a cell. Signal transduction begins with reception of a signal (e.g. a ligand binding to a receptor or receptor activation by a stimulus such as light), or for signal transduction in the absence of ligand, signal-withdrawal or the activity of a constitutively active receptor. Signal transduction ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. regulation of transcription or regulation of a metabolic process. Signal transduction covers signaling from receptors located on the surface of the cell and signaling via molecules located within the cell. For signaling between cells, signal transduction is restricted to events at and within the receiving cell.

name: protoheme IX farnesyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: protoheme IX + (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate + H2O = heme o + diphosphate.

name: negative regulation of cell adhesion
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell adhesion.

name: translation activator activity
description: Any of a group of soluble proteins functioning in the activation of ribosome-mediated translation of mRNA into a polypeptide.

name: establishment or maintenance of cell polarity
description: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of anisotropic intracellular organization or cell growth patterns.

name: tetracycline transporter activity
description: Enables the directed movement of tetracycline into, out of or within a cell, or between cells. Tetracycline is a broad spectrum antibiotic that blocks binding of aminoacyl tRNA to the ribosomes of both Gram-positive and Gram-negative organisms (and those of organelles).

name: receptor guanylyl cyclase signaling pathway
description: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of an extracellular ligand to a receptor on the surface of the target cell where the receptor possesses guanylyl cyclase activity, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase signaling pathway
description: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of an extracellular ligand to a receptor on the surface of the target cell where the receptor possesses tyrosine kinase activity, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: UDP-galactose:beta-N-acetylglucosamine beta-1,3-galactosyltransferase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-galactose + N-acetylglucosamine = galactose-beta-1,3-N-acetylglucosamine + UDP.

name: cell surface receptor signaling pathway
description: A series of molecular signals initiated by activation of a receptor on the surface of a cell. The pathway begins with binding of an extracellular ligand to a cell surface receptor, or for receptors that signal in the absence of a ligand, by ligand-withdrawal or the activity of a constitutively active receptor. The pathway ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: enzyme linked receptor protein signaling pathway
description: Any series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of an extracellular ligand to a receptor on the surface of the target cell, where the receptor possesses catalytic activity or is closely associated with an enzyme such as a protein kinase, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: oxalic acid secretion
description: The controlled release of oxalic acid, ethanedioic acid, by a cell or a tissue.

name: deoxyhypusine monooxygenase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: protein N6-(4-aminobutyl)-L-lysine + donor-H2 + O2 = protein N6-((R)-4-amino-2-hydroxybutyl)-L-lysine + acceptor + H2O.

name: cytosolic aryl hydrocarbon receptor complex
description: An aryl hydrocarbon receptor complex found in the cytosol, in which the ligand-binding subunit AhR is not bound to ligand; consists of AhR, two molecules of HSP90, the protein kinase c-Src, and the immunophilin XAP2/AIP.

name: iron ion transmembrane transport
description: A process in which an iron ion is transported from one side of a membrane to the other by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

name: phosphatidylinositol phosphate binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with phosphatidylinositol phosphate.

name: negative regulation of protein acetylation
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein acetylation.

name: positive regulation of cell cycle phase transition
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell cycle phase transition.

name: regulation of inward rectifier potassium channel activity
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of inward rectifier potassium channel activity.

name: cellular response to BMP stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a bone morphogenetic protein (BMP) stimulus.

name: integrin alphaIIb-beta3 complex
description: An integrin complex that comprises one alphaIIb subunit and one beta3 subunit.

name: photoreceptor cell maintenance
description: Any process preventing the degeneration of the photoreceptor, a specialized cell type that is sensitive to light.

name: regulation of oligodendrocyte progenitor proliferation
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of oligodendrocyte progenitor proliferation.

name: response to fibroblast growth factor
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a fibroblast growth factor stimulus.

name: elongin complex
description: A transcription elongation factor complex that suppresses RNA polymerase II pausing, and may act by promoting proper alignment of the 3'-end of nascent transcripts with the polymerase catalytic site. Consists of a transcriptionally active Elongin A subunit (abut 100 kDa)and two smaller Elongin B (about 18 kDa) and Elongin C (about 15 kDa)subunits.

name: cholesterol biosynthetic process via lathosterol
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of cholesterol, cholest-5-en-3 beta-ol, via the intermediate lathosterol.

name: regulation of mitotic cell cycle phase transition
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mitotic cell cycle phase transition.

name: ferulate metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving ferulate, (2E)-3-(4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl)prop-2-enoate.

name: negative regulation of mitotic cell cycle phase transition
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mitotic cell cycle phase transition.

name: negative regulation of meiotic cell cycle phase transition
description: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of meiotic cell cycle phase transition.

name: chemorepellent activity
description: Providing the environmental signal that initiates the directed movement of a motile cell or organism towards a lower concentration of that signal.

name: toxin transport
description: The directed movement of a toxin into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

name: positive regulation of nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 1 signaling pathway
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of the nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 1 (NOD1) pathway.

name: nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 2 signaling pathway
description: Any series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of binding to nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 2 (NOD2).

name: positive regulation of nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 2 signaling pathway
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of the nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 2 (NOD2) pathway.

name: cholesterol biosynthetic process via 24,25-dihydrolanosterol
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of cholesterol, cholest-5-en-3 beta-ol, via the intermediate 24,25-dihydrolanosterol.

name: Shc-EGFR complex
description: A protein complex that contains the epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) and the adaptor protein Shc, and is involved in linking EGFR activation to the p21-Ras pathway.

name: nuclear membrane organization
description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the nuclear inner or outer membrane.

name: negative regulation of nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 2 signaling pathway
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of the nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 2 (NOD2) pathway.

name: Grb2-EGFR complex
description: A protein complex that contains the epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) and Grb2, and is involved in linking EGFR activation to the p21-Ras pathway.

name: adenylate cyclase-inhibiting G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway
description: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a G-protein coupled receptor binding to its physiological ligand, where the pathway proceeds through inhibition of adenylyl cyclase activity and a subsequent decrease in the concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP).

name: negative regulation of adenylate cyclase activity
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of adenylate cyclase activity.

name: adenylate cyclase-activating dopamine receptor signaling pathway
description: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a dopamine receptor binding to its physiological ligand, where the pathway proceeds with activation of adenylyl cyclase and a subsequent increase in the concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP).

name: adenylate cyclase-inhibiting G-protein coupled acetylcholine receptor signaling pathway
description: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a G-protein coupled acetylcholine receptor binding to its physiological ligand, where the pathway proceeds with inhibition of adenylyl cyclase and a subsequent decrease in the concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP).

name: adenylate cyclase-inhibiting serotonin receptor signaling pathway
description: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a serotonin receptor binding to its physiological ligand, where the pathway proceeds with inhibition of adenylyl cyclase and a subsequent decrease in the concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP).

name: cleavage furrow
description: The cleavage furrow is a plasma membrane invagination at the cell division site. The cleavage furrow begins as a shallow groove and eventually deepens to divide the cytoplasm.

name: nitric oxide homeostasis
description: A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of nitric oxide within an organism or cell.

name: adenylate cyclase-inhibiting dopamine receptor signaling pathway
description: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a dopamine receptor binding to its physiological ligand, where the pathway proceeds with inhibition of adenylyl cyclase and a subsequent decrease in the concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP).

name: adenylate cyclase-inhibiting G-protein coupled glutamate receptor signaling pathway
description: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a G-protein coupled glutamate receptor binding to its physiological ligand, where the pathway proceeds with inhibition of adenylyl cyclase and a subsequent decrease in the concentration of cyclic AMP (cAMP).

name: G-protein coupled receptor signaling pathway coupled to cGMP nucleotide second messenger
description: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a G-protein coupled receptor binding to its physiological ligand, followed by activation of guanylyl cyclase (GC) activity and a subsequent increase in the concentration of cyclic GMP (cGMP).

name: chemokine (C-C motif) ligand 5 binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with chemokine (C-C motif) ligand 5.

name: protein binding involved in protein folding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any protein or protein complex (a complex of two or more proteins that may include other nonprotein molecules) that contributes to the process of protein folding.

name: tubulin-dependent ATPase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + H2O = ADP + phosphate. This reaction requires the presence of a tubulin dimer to accelerate release of ADP and phosphate.

name: snRNA-activating protein complex
description: A protein complex that recognizes the proximal sequence element of RNA polymerase II and III snRNA promoters.

name: SAGA-type complex
description: A histone acetyltransferase complex that acetylates nucleosomal H3 and H2B and is required for the expression of a subset of Pol II-transcribed genes. The budding yeast complex includes the acetyltransferase Gcn5p, several proteins of the Spt and Ada families, and several TBP-associate proteins (TAFs); analogous complexes in other species have analogous compositions, and usually contain homologs of the yeast proteins.

name: plus-end specific microtubule depolymerization
description: The removal of tubulin heterodimers from the plus end of a microtubule.

name: activation of protein kinase activity
description: Any process that initiates the activity of an inactive protein kinase.

name: cellular response to prostaglandin D stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a prostagladin D stimulus.

name: 4-aminobutyrate transaminase complex
description: A homodimeric protein complex that possesses 4-aminobutyrate transaminase activity.

name: K6-linked polyubiquitin binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently and non-covalently with a polymer of ubiquitin formed by linkages between lysine residues at position 6 of the ubiquitin monomers.

name: succinate-semialdehyde dehydrogenase binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with succinate-semialdehyde dehydrogenase.

name: LUBAC complex
description: A ubiquitin ligase complex that catalyzes linear head-to-tail polyubiquitin conjugation on its targets. In human the complex consists of RBCK1, RNF31 and SHARPIN, and has an MW of approximately 600 kDa, suggesting a heteromultimeric assembly of its subunits. LUBAC stands for Linear Ubiquitin Chain Assembly Complex.

name: activation of adenylate cyclase activity
description: Any process that initiates the activity of the inactive enzyme adenylate cyclase.

name: respiratory chain
description: The protein complexes that form the electron transport system (the respiratory chain), associated with a cell membrane, usually the plasma membrane (in prokaryotes) or the inner mitochondrial membrane (on eukaryotes). The respiratory chain complexes transfer electrons from an electron donor to an electron acceptor and are associated with a proton pump to create a transmembrane electrochemical gradient.

name: activation of protein kinase B activity
description: Any process that initiates the activity of the inactive enzyme protein kinase B.

name: single guanine insertion binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with double-stranded DNA containing a single guanine insertion or a deletion that results in an unpaired guanine.

name: single thymine insertion binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with double-stranded DNA containing a single thymine insertion or a deletion that results in an unpaired thymine.

name: cytolytic granule
description: A specialized secretory lysosome that is present in cells with cytolytic capability such as cytotoxic T lymphocytes and natural killer cells. Cytolytic granules mediate the storage and regulated excretion of lytic molecules for killing of target cells.

name: endoplasmic reticulum tubular network
description: A subcompartment of the endoplasmic reticulum consisting of tubules having membranes with high curvature in cross-section.

name: chromosome passenger complex
description: A eukaryotically conserved protein complex that localizes to kinetochores in early mitosis, the spindle mid-zone in anaphase B and to the telophase midbody. It has been proposed that the passenger complex coordinates various events based on its location to different structures during the course of mitosis. Complex members include the BIR-domain-containing protein Survivin, Aurora kinase, INCENP and Borealin.

name: endoplasmic reticulum tubular network organization
description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) tubular network. The ER tubular network is the ER part that that has membranes with high curvature in cross-section.

name: dinucleotide insertion or deletion binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with double-stranded DNA containing a dinucleotide insertion or deletion.

name: guanine/thymine mispair binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with double-stranded DNA containing a G/T mispair.

name: cellular detoxification of nitrogen compound
description: Any cellular process that reduces or removes the toxicity of nitrogenous compounds which are dangerous or toxic. This includes the aerobic conversion of toxic compounds to harmless substances.

name: single base insertion or deletion binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with double-stranded DNA containing a single base insertion or deletion.

name: prolactin secretion
description: The regulated release of prolactin, a peptide hormone that stimulates lactation, from secretory granules in the anterior pituitary.

name: carbamoyl phosphate biosynthetic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of carbamoyl phosphate, an intermediate in the urea cycle and other nitrogen compound metabolic pathways.

name: oxidation-dependent protein catabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein or peptide by hydrolysis of its peptide bonds, initiated by the oxidation of one or more amino acid residues in the protein.

name: myoblast differentiation
description: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a myoblast. A myoblast is a mononucleate cell type that, by fusion with other myoblasts, gives rise to the myotubes that eventually develop into striated muscle fibers.

name: endothelial cell differentiation
description: The process in which a mesodermal, bone marrow or neural crest cell acquires specialized features of an endothelial cell, a thin flattened cell. A layer of such cells lines the inside surfaces of body cavities, blood vessels, and lymph vessels, making up the endothelium.

name: protein autophosphorylation
description: The phosphorylation by a protein of one or more of its own amino acid residues (cis-autophosphorylation), or residues on an identical protein (trans-autophosphorylation).

name: fat cell differentiation
description: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an adipocyte, an animal connective tissue cell specialized for the synthesis and storage of fat.

name: growth of symbiont in host
description: The increase in size or mass of an organism, occurring within the cells or tissues of the host organism. This may (but not necessarily) include a filamentous growth form, and also can include secretion of proteases and lipases to break down host tissue. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

name: modification by virus of host mRNA processing
description: Any viral process that interferes with the processing of mRNA in the host cell.

name: bone resorption
description: The process in which specialized cells known as osteoclasts degrade the organic and inorganic portions of bone, and endocytose and transport the degradation products.

name: viral mRNA export from host cell nucleus
description: The directed movement of intronless viral mRNA from the host nucleus to the cytoplasm for translation.

name: regulation of viral transcription
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the transcription of the viral genome.

name: NADP+ binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the oxidized form, NADP+, of nicotinamide-adenine dinucleotide phosphate, a coenzyme involved in many redox and biosynthetic reactions.

name: cellular response to nitric oxide
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a nitric oxide stimulus.

name: NADPH binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the reduced form, NADPH, of nicotinamide-adenine dinucleotide phosphate, a coenzyme involved in many redox and biosynthetic reactions.

name: transcriptional activation by promoter-enhancer looping
description: The formation and maintenance of DNA loops that juxtapose the promoter and enhancer regions of RNA polymerase II-transcribed genes and activate transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

name: response to nitric oxide
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a nitric oxide stimulus.

name: NAD+ binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the oxidized form, NAD, of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide, a coenzyme involved in many redox and biosynthetic reactions.

name: NADH binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the reduced form, NADH, of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide, a coenzyme involved in many redox and biosynthetic reactions.

name: cellular response to triacyl bacterial lipopeptide
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a triacylated bacterial lipopeptide stimulus.

name: microtubule polymerization
description: The addition of tubulin heterodimers to one or both ends of a microtubule.

name: cell redox homeostasis
description: Any process that maintains the redox environment of a cell or compartment within a cell.

name: host cell surface receptor binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a receptor on the host cell surface.

name: positive regulation of monocyte aggregation
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of monocyte aggregation.

name: virion binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a virion, either by binding to components of the capsid or the viral envelope.

name: negative regulation of growth of symbiont in host
description: Any process in which the symbiont stops, prevents or reduces its increase in size or mass within the cells or tissues of the host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in the symbiotic interaction.

name: cellular response to diacyl bacterial lipopeptide
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a diacylated bacterial lipopeptide stimulus.

name: lipopeptide binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a lipopeptide, any of a group of organic compounds comprising two or more amino acids linked by peptide bonds and containing a nonprotein group consisting of a lipid or lipids.

name: negative regulation of nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 1 signaling pathway
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of the nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 1 (NOD1) pathway.

name: S-adenosyl-L-methionine transmembrane transport
description: The directed movement of S-adenosyl-L-methionine across a membrane.

name: acrosin binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with acrosin, a protein that is found in the acrosomes of sperm and possesses protease and carbohydrate binding activities.

name: response to ethanol
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an ethanol stimulus.

name: negative regulation of growth of symbiont on or near host surface
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the increase in the symbiont's size or mass on or near the cells or tissues of the host organism.

name: locomotor rhythm
description: The rhythm of the locomotor activity of an organism during its 24 hour activity cycle.

name: response to ether
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a ether stimulus.

name: nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing signaling pathway
description: Any series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of binding to a nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing (NOD) protein.

name: regulation of nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing signaling pathway
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of a nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing (NOD) pathway.

name: nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 1 signaling pathway
description: Any series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of binding to nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain containing 1 (NOD1).

name: SUMO binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the small ubiquitin-like protein SUMO.

name: nonhomologous end joining complex
description: A protein complex that plays a role in DNA double-strand break repair via nonhomologous end joining. Such complexes typically contain a specialized DNA ligase (e.g. Lig4 in eukaryotes) and one or more proteins that bind to DNA ends.

name: dinucleotide repeat insertion binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with double-stranded DNA containing a dinucleotide repeat insertion or a deletion resulting in unpaired dinucleotide repeats.

name: SUMO polymer binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a polymer of the small ubiquitin-like protein SUMO.

name: septin cytoskeleton organization
description: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising septin complexes and their associated proteins.

name: negative regulation of growth of symbiont involved in interaction with host
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the increase in size or mass of an organism occurring in, on or near the exterior of its host organism.

name: regulation of cell cycle checkpoint
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell cycle checkpoint.

name: positive regulation of cell cycle checkpoint
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell cycle checkpoint.

name: histone H3-K14 acetylation
description: The modification of histone H3 by the addition of an acetyl group to a lysine residue at position 14 of the histone.

name: R-SMAD binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a receptor-regulated SMAD signaling protein.

name: co-SMAD binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a common mediator SMAD signaling protein.

name: I-SMAD binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an inhibitory SMAD signaling protein.

name: cellular response to cold
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a cold stimulus, a temperature stimulus below the optimal temperature for that organism.

name: cellular response to UV-B
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a UV-B radiation stimulus. UV-B radiation (UV-B light) spans the wavelengths 280 to 315 nm.

name: cellular response to UV-C
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a UV-C radiation stimulus. UV-C radiation (UV-C light) spans the wavelengths 100 to 280 nm.

name: cellular response to UV-A
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a UV-A radiation stimulus. UV-A radiation (UV-A light) spans the wavelengths 315 to 400 nm.

name: enamel mineralization
description: The process in which calcium salts, mainly carbonated hydroxyapatite, are deposited in tooth enamel.

name: cellular response to fluid shear stress
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a fluid shear stress stimulus. Fluid shear stress is the force acting on an object in a system where the fluid is moving across a solid surface.

name: negative regulation of adiponectin secretion
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of adiponectin from a cell.

name: positive regulation of adiponectin secretion
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of adiponectin from a cell.

name: negative regulation of biomineral tissue development
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of biomineral tissue development, the formation of hard tissues that consist mainly of inorganic compounds.

name: cellular response to laminar fluid shear stress
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a laminar fluid shear stress stimulus. Laminar fluid flow is the force acting on an object in a system where the fluid is moving across a solid surface in parallel layers.

name: cellular response to light stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a light stimulus, electromagnetic radiation of wavelengths classified as infrared, visible or ultraviolet light.

name: cellular response to gamma radiation
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a gamma radiation stimulus. Gamma radiation is a form of electromagnetic radiation (EMR) or light emission of a specific frequency produced from sub-atomic particle interaction, such as electron-positron annihilation and radioactive decay. Gamma rays are generally characterized as EMR having the highest frequency and energy, and also the shortest wavelength, within the electromagnetic radiation spectrum.

name: cellular response to X-ray
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of X-ray radiation. An X-ray is a form of electromagnetic radiation with a wavelength in the range of 10 nanometers to 100 picometers (corresponding to frequencies in the range 30 PHz to 3 EHz).

name: mitochondrial threonyl-tRNA aminoacylation
description: The process of coupling threonine to threonyl-tRNA in a mitochondrion, catalyzed by threonyl-tRNA synthetase. In tRNA aminoacylation, the amino acid is first activated by linkage to AMP and then transferred to either the 2'- or the 3'-hydroxyl group of the 3'-adenosine residue of the tRNA.

name: methionine-R-sulfoxide reductase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: L-methionine R-oxide + thioredoxin = L-methionine + thioredoxin disulfide; can act on free oxidized methionine with specificity for the R enantiomer; does not act on oxidized methionine in peptide linkage. Thioredoxin disulfide is the oxidized form of thioredoxin.

name: mitochondrial tyrosyl-tRNA aminoacylation
description: The process of coupling tyrosine to tyrosyl-tRNA in a mitochondrion, catalyzed by tyrosyl-tRNA synthetase. In tRNA aminoacylation, the amino acid is first activated by linkage to AMP and then transferred to either the 2'- or the 3'-hydroxyl group of the 3'-adenosine residue of the tRNA.

name: DNA polymerase binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a DNA polymerase.

name: kynurenine metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving kynurenine, the amino acid 3-(2-aminobenzoyl)-alanine.

name: response to hydroperoxide
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a hydroperoxide stimulus. Hydroperoxides are monosubstitution products of hydrogen peroxide, HOOH.

name: Lsd1/2 complex
description: A nucleosome-binding protein complex that comprises two SWIRM domain histone demethylases and two PHD finger proteins. The complex is involved in transcriptional regulation via heterochromatic silencing and the regulation of chromatin boundary formation, and was first identified in fission yeast.

name: calmodulin-dependent protein phosphatase activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: protein serine/threonine phosphate + H2O = protein serine/threonine + phosphate, dependent on the presence of calcium-bound calmodulin.

name: response to ATP
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an ATP (adenosine 5'-triphosphate) stimulus.

name: response to vitamin E
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a vitamin E stimulus.

name: small ribosomal subunit rRNA binding
description: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the small ribosomal subunit RNA (SSU rRNA), a constituent of the small ribosomal subunit. In S. cerevisiae, this is the 18S rRNA.

name: regulation of enamel mineralization
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of enamel mineralization, the deposition of calcium salts in tooth enamel.

name: negative regulation of tooth mineralization
description: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of tooth mineralization, the deposition of calcium salts in tooth structures.

name: positive regulation of tooth mineralization
description: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of tooth mineralization, the deposition of calcium salts in tooth structures.

name: D-serine metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving D-serine, the D-enantiomer of serine, i.e. (2R)-2-amino-3-hydroxypropanoic acid.

name: DRM complex
description: A transcriptional repressor complex that contains the lin-9, lin-35, lin-37, lin-52, lin-53, lin-5is involved in 4-, dpl-1 and efl-1 proteins, and is involved in cell fate specification.

name: D-serine biosynthetic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of D-serine, the D-enantiomer of serine, i.e. (2R)-2-amino-3-hydroxypropanoic acid. D-serine is often formed by racemization of L-serine.

name: response to vitamin A
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a vitamin A stimulus.

name: S-adenosylmethioninamine metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving S-adenosylmethioninamine, (5-deoxy-5-adenosyl)(3-aminopropyl) methylsulfonium salt.

name: glutathione dehydrogenase (ascorbate) activity
description: Catalysis of the reaction: dehydroascorbate + 2 glutathione = L-ascorbate + glutathione disulfide.

name: intercellular bridge
description: A direct connection between the cytoplasm of two cells that is formed following the completion of cleavage furrow ingression during cell division. They are usually present only briefly prior to completion of cytokinesis. However, in some cases, such as the bridges between germ cells during their development, they become stabilised.

name: apical part of cell
description: The region of a polarized cell that forms a tip or is distal to a base. For example, in a polarized epithelial cell, the apical region has an exposed surface and lies opposite to the basal lamina that separates the epithelium from other tissue.

name: cellular response to oxygen levels
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus reflecting the presence, absence, or concentration of oxygen.

name: basal part of cell
description: The region of a cell situated near the base. For example, in a polarized epithelial cell, the basal surface rests on the basal lamina that separates the epithelium from other tissue.

name: transforming growth factor beta receptor activity, type III
description: Combining with transforming growth factor beta to initiate a change in cell activity; facilitates ligand binding to type I and type II TGF-beta receptors.

name: basal protein localization
description: Any process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, basal regions of the cell.

name: ciliary neurotrophic factor-mediated signaling pathway
description: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a ciliary neurotrophic factor (CNTF) to a receptor on the surface of a cell, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

name: apical protein localization
